{"metadata":{"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"scrolled","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"done"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"modules":[{"name":"UltraliteSDK"}],"symbolKind":"method","title":"scrolled(done:)","roleHeading":"Instance Method","externalID":"s:12UltraliteSDK12ScrollLayoutC12AutoScrollerC8scrolled4doneySb_tF"},"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller\/scrolled(done:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"scrolled","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"done"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"]}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout\/autoscroller\/scrolled(done:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"delegate callback."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK","doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout","doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller"]]},"sections":[],"references":{"doc://UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK/ScrollLayout/AutoScroller/scrolled(done:)":{"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"scrolled"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"done","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout\/autoscroller\/scrolled(done:)","title":"scrolled(done:)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"delegate callback."}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller\/scrolled(done:)","role":"symbol"},"doc://UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this SDK to easily send text and images to your Vuxix smart glasses."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK","kind":"symbol","title":"UltraliteSDK","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk"},"doc://UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK/ScrollLayout/AutoScroller":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"AutoScroller is a utility class to send a large known block of predfined text to the glasses to be smoothly scrolled."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This is simlar to what is seen on a teleprompter or in movie credits."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This class was written using the "},{"code":"ScrollLayout","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" commands and is nothing more than a convience class."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Everything used this class can be written from the public SDK.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It scrolls the text much like a teleprompter would with basic commands to pause and resume the scrolling.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"The duration (speed) of the scrolling can be modified while scrolling by seting the ","type":"text"},{"code":"duration","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" property."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It can support any language that the font supports."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If the content is not known up front, or subject to change, this is the utility class will not work (use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"LiveText"},{"type":"text","text":" instance instead)."}],"url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout\/autoscroller","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"AutoScroller","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"ScrollLayout.AutoScroller","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AutoScroller","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK/ScrollLayout":{"abstract":[{"text":"When Ultralite.requestControl with a .scroll layout type .. this is the class you interate with to draw scrolling text to the screen.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Once the layout is .scrolled you must send one configure message to tell the layout how to setup.  It will setup the slice height and how many slices are visible."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"There are two supported modes: autoScroll on\/off"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"When autoScroll is true, the slices are automatically scrolled.  Subscribe to the delgate and listen for the scrolled callback, when you get it send another slice of text","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"When autoScroll is false, you can drive the slices and how they look on the screen.  You can send all the slices at once or send one at a time and animate it onto the screen at the current time."}],"url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout","kind":"symbol","title":"ScrollLayout","role":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ScrollLayout","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ScrollLayout","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout"}}}